records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 2, forgery.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 3, forgery and theft.  Motion granted.
The State also moves to read in an uncharged referral for possess THC, incident no: M14-11846.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four and one half (4.5) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Defendant is to continue his mental health treatment;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
5) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law,  commencing immediately;
7) Pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) defendant is to take all medications as prescribed and in the prescribed doses;
10) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
11) pay restitution of $1,025.00 to United One Credit Union at 1117 S. 10th Street, Manitowoc, WI;
Restitution is to be paid at the rate of at least $75.00 per month.  The agent may modify the amount higher if feels defendant can comply.  Any restitution payments are to be applied to the restitution owing in 14 CM 465 first.
Settlement Conference Summary.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
Minutes.
